etymology.description: 禾(禾) (hé, "grain") + 朮(朮) (zhú, "glutinous millet") = grain with phonetic "glutinous millet" -> glutinous millet
etymology.interpretation: The character 秫 (shú, "glutinous millet") combines 禾(禾) (hé, "grain") to signify its association with grains, and 朮(朮) (zhú, "glutinous millet") for its phonetic value, representing the specific type of grain, glutinous millet.
